Fond farewell to Butterley Engineering works
Please turn on JavaScript. Media requires JavaScript to play. Advertisement
The site of the former Butterley Engineering works near Ripley, Derbyshire, has finally succumbed to the demolition men. BBC East Midlands Today's James Roberson reminds us how the company was a major iron works provider for more than two centuries and had a hand in the construction of many iconic buildings, including St Pancras Station, Vauxhall Bridge, Portsmouth's Spinnaker Tower, the Falkirk Wheel and many more. In pictures: A short history of Butterley Engineering
