Brechin City 1-0 Cowdenbeath
Brechin City had to make do with fourth place and a promotion play-off against Airdrie United after Paddy Connolly's goal secured victory over Cowdenbeath.
Kevin Byers fired a 25-yard drive against the post before the break. Paddy Connolly turned on a Grant Johnson pass and fired the ball into the net after 72 minutes.
Gary Kenneth went close to equalising with a powerful drive before Cowden's David Armstrong and Douglas Hill were sent off in a stormy finale.
